  • Method Details

    • tryEditCamp

      public static boolean tryEditCamp(Camp camp, int category, String change)
      Checks whether the change suggested is legal. Does not edit the camp.
      The change is to be supplied as a String, tryEditCamp() will attempt the appropriate conversions.
      If illegal, it will print a message to the User explaining why.
      Separated from DoEditCamp for use in the Suggestions feature.
      When used by Staff, a true return means it is safe to call DoEditCamp with the same parameters
      Parameters:
      camp - Camp to be edited
      category - Category assigned int to change.
      change - The change to be made. Regardless of the data type, this is always a String.
      Returns:
      Boolean on whether change is legal. Returns true for legal.

    • doEditCamp

      public static void doEditCamp(Camp camp, int category, String change)
      Sibling of tryEditCamp(). IMPORTANT: doEditCamp() assumes that the change is legal and possible from tryEditCamp. Fatal error possible if doEditCamp() is called without checking.
      Parameters:
      camp - Camp to be edited
      category - Category assigned int to change.
      change - LEGAL change to be made.
